  "intros": "<div class=\"tabs-container\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-800 mb-6 mt-6 text-center\">Lesson 7: Writing Your First Line of Code with `console.log()`</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-gray-600 text-lg mb-8 text-center px-4\">It's time to write our very first JavaScript command and see it in action. Let's make the computer talk back to us!</p>\n\n    <!-- Hidden radio buttons that control the state of the tabs -->\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"tab1\" name=\"tabs\" class=\"hidden\" checked>\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"tab2\" name=\"tabs\" class=\"hidden\">\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"tab3\" name=\"tabs\" class=\"hidden\">\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"tab4\" name=\"tabs\" class=\"hidden\">\n    <input type=\"radio\" id=\"tab5\" name=\"tabs\" class=\"hidden\">\n\n    <!-- Tab Header Buttons (styled labels) -->\n    <div class=\"tabs-header flex flex-row bg-gray-100 border-b border-gray-200 text-sm font-medium text-center text-gray-600 rounded-t-lg overflow-hidden\">\n        <label for=\"tab1\" class=\"tab-label\" id=\"label1\" title=\"The Walkie-Talkie\">1</label>\n        <label for=\"tab2\" class=\"tab-label\" id=\"label2\" title=\"The Status Report\">2</label>\n        <label for=\"tab3\" class=\"tab-label\" id=\"label3\" title=\"The Lab Assistant\">3</label>\n        <label for=\"tab4\" class=\"tab-label\" id=\"label4\" title=\"The 'Are We There Yet?'\">4</label>\n        <label for=\"tab5\" class=\"tab-label\" id=\"label5\" title=\"The Lighthouse Beam\">5</label>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Tab Content Panels -->\n    <div class=\"tab-content-container p-6 sm:p-8 border border-t-0 border-gray-200 rounded-b-lg\">\n        <!-- Tab 1 Content: The Walkie-Talkie -->\n        <div class=\"tab-content content1\" id=\"content1\">\n            <h3 class=\"intro-title text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3\">The Walkie-Talkie</h3>\n            <h2 class=\"intro-question text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4\">You've sent a scout into a dark forest. How do you know if they've arrived safely?</h2>\n            <div class=\"description-container flex flex-col justify-center w-full mb-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg shadow-inner\">\n                <svg width=\"100%\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"bg-white rounded-md shadow-sm\">\n                    <rect width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" fill=\"#ffffff\" />\n                    <!-- Developer (You) -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(400, 450)\">\n                        <circle cx=\"0\" cy=\"0\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#e0f2fe\"/>\n                        <path d=\"M-40 40 l80 0 l-40 80 Z\" fill=\"#3b82f6\"/>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"200\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#374151\" text-anchor=\"middle\">You</text>\n                    </g>\n                    <!-- Walkie Talkie -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(800, 450)\">\n                        <rect x=\"-60\" y=\"-120\" width=\"120\" height=\"240\" rx=\"15\" fill=\"#1f2937\"/>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-50\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"24\" fill=\"#6ee7b7\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\"Scout, report!\"</text>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"50\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"24\" fill=\"#fcd34d\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\"Copy, I'm here.\"</text>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"250\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#0ea5e9\" text-anchor=\"middle\">The Console</text>\n                    </g>\n                    <!-- Scout (JavaScript file) -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(1200, 450)\">\n                        <path d=\"M-100,100 L 0,-150 L 100,100 Z\" fill=\"#22c55e\" opacity=\"0.5\"/>\n                        <circle cx=\"0\" cy=\"0\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#f0fdf4\"/>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"200\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#374151\" text-anchor=\"middle\">JavaScript File</text>\n                    </g>\n                </svg>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-8\">\n                    When you link a JavaScript file, you are sending it into the \"dark forest\" of the browser to do a job. But how do you confirm it got there and is running correctly? You can't see it on the main page. You need a way for it to report back to you.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4\">\n                    The command <code class=\"bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-1 rounded\">console.log()</code> is your walkie-talkie. It's a special instruction that tells your JavaScript file: \"Send a message back to home base.\" The \"home base\" is the Developer Console. By writing <code class=\"bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-1 rounded\">console.log(\"I'm here!\")</code>, your script sends that exact message to the console, confirming that it's loaded and running. It's the simplest and most essential way to check if your code is alive.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-tagline mt-6 text-center font-semibold text-sky-600 italic\">`console.log()` is your script's way of saying \"I'm alive and ready for orders!\"</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <!-- Tab 2 Content: The Status Report -->\n        <div class=\"tab-content content2\" id=\"content2\">\n            <h3 class=\"intro-title text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3\">The Status Report</h3>\n            <h2 class=\"intro-question text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4\">You've given a team a task. How do you get updates on their progress without constantly interrupting them?</h2>\n            <div class=\"description-container flex flex-col justify-center w-full mb-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg shadow-inner\">\n                 <svg width=\"100%\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"bg-white rounded-md shadow-sm\">\n                    <rect width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" fill=\"#ffffff\" />\n                    <!-- Your Code (The Task) -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(450, 450)\">\n                        <rect x=\"-200\" y=\"-250\" width=\"400\" height=\"500\" fill=\"#f1f5f9\" rx=\"10\"/>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-200\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#374151\" text-anchor=\"middle\">The Task</text>\n                        <text x=\"-150\" y=\"-100\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"24\">Step 1...</text>\n                        <text x=\"-150\" y=\"-50\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"24\">Step 2...</text>\n                        <text x=\"-150\" y=\"0\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"24\">Step 3...</text>\n                    </g>\n                    <!-- Arrow -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(800, 450)\">\n                        <path d=\"M-50,0 l100,0\" stroke=\"#0ea5e9\" stroke-width=\"8\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/>\n                        <path d=\"M30,-20 l20,20 l-20,20\" stroke=\"#0ea5e9\" stroke-width=\"8\" fill=\"none\"/>\n                    </g>\n                    <!-- Status Report (Console) -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(1150, 450)\">\n                        <rect x=\"-200\" y=\"-250\" width=\"400\" height=\"500\" fill=\"#1e293b\" rx=\"10\"/>\n                         <text x=\"0\" y=\"-200\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"white\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Status Report</text>\n                         <text x=\"-150\" y=\"-100\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"24\" fill=\"#6ee7b7\">> Step 1 complete.</text>\n                         <text x=\"-150\" y=\"-50\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"24\" fill=\"#f87171\">> Error in Step 2!</text>\n                         <text x=\"-150\" y=\"0\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"24\" fill=\"#9ca3af\">> Halting process.</text>\n                    </g>\n                </svg>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-8\">\n                    Imagine your JavaScript code is a diligent team working through a list of tasks. You, as the manager, want to know what they're doing. Instead of constantly looking over their shoulder (which is impossible anyway), you ask them to leave notes on a central whiteboard as they complete each step.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4\">\n                    The Developer Console is that whiteboard, and <code class=\"bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-1 rounded\">console.log()</code> is the marker they use to write on it. You can sprinkle `console.log()` statements throughout your code to act as status reports. For example: <code class=\"bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-1 rounded\">console.log(\"Starting calculation...\")</code>, and then later, <code class=\"bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-1 rounded\">console.log(\"Calculation complete!\")</code>. This lets you watch the flow of your program and pinpoint exactly where things are working and where they might be failing.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-tagline mt-6 text-center font-semibold text-sky-600 italic\">`console.log()` is your code's way of giving you a live status update.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        \n        <!-- Tab 3 Content: The Lab Assistant -->\n        <div class=\"tab-content content3\" id=\"content3\">\n            <h3 class=\"intro-title text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3\">The Lab Assistant</h3>\n            <h2 class=\"intro-question text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4\">You're a scientist mixing chemicals. How do you know what's inside a beaker without contaminating it?</h2>\n            <div class=\"description-container flex flex-col justify-center w-full mb-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg shadow-inner\">\n                <svg width=\"100%\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"bg-white rounded-md shadow-sm\">\n                    <rect width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" fill=\"#ffffff\" />\n                    <!-- Your Code (Beaker) -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(450, 450)\">\n                        <path d=\"M-100,200 L -150,-200 L 150,-200 L 100,200 Z\" fill=\"#e0f2fe\"/>\n                        <path d=\"M-135,-150 C -50,-50 50,-50 -135,-150\" fill=\"#3b82f6\"/>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"300\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#374151\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Your Code's \"Memory\"</text>\n                    </g>\n                    <!-- Arrow -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(800, 450)\">\n                        <path d=\"M-50,0 l100,0\" stroke=\"#0ea5e9\" stroke-width=\"8\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"/>\n                        <path d=\"M30,-20 l20,20 l-20,20\" stroke=\"#0ea5e9\" stroke-width=\"8\" fill=\"none\"/>\n                    </g>\n                    <!-- Lab Assistant (Console) -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(1150, 450)\">\n                        <circle cx=\"0\" cy=\"0\" r=\"40\" fill=\"#f0fdf4\"/>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"100\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"24\" font-weight=\"bold\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Lab Assistant</text>\n                        <rect x=\"-150\" y=\"-200\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" fill=\"#1f2937\" rx=\"10\"/>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-140\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"24\" fill=\"white\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\"The value is: 42\"</text>\n                        <text x=\"0\" y=\"-250\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"#374151\" text-anchor=\"middle\">The Console</text>\n                    </g>\n                </svg>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-8\">\n                    In programming, you will constantly store information in things called \"variables\"â€”they are like the beakers in your lab. You might have a variable holding a user's name, or the result of a math problem. Often, you need to check what's inside that beaker at a specific moment in your experiment.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4\">\n                    You can't just \"look\" at it. You need a tool. Think of <code class=\"bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-1 rounded\">console.log()</code> as your tireless lab assistant. You can ask it, \"Hey, what's in the 'userScore' beaker right now?\" by writing <code class=\"bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-1 rounded\">console.log(userScore)</code>. The assistant will then go, take a perfect sample without disturbing the experiment, and report the exact contents back to you in the console window. It's the cleanest way to inspect the state of your program.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-tagline mt-6 text-center font-semibold text-sky-600 italic\">`console.log()` is your personal assistant for inspecting your code's inner state.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        \n        <!-- Tab 4 Content: The 'Are We There Yet?' -->\n        <div class=\"tab-content content4\" id=\"content4\">\n            <h3 class=\"intro-title text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3\">The \"Are We There Yet?\"</h3>\n            <h2 class=\"intro-question text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4\">On a long road trip, how do you know which towns you've passed through?</h2>\n            <div class=\"description-container flex flex-col justify-center w-full mb-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg shadow-inner\">\n                <svg width=\"100%\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"bg-white rounded-md shadow-sm\">\n                    <rect width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" fill=\"#ffffff\" />\n                    <!-- Road -->\n                    <path d=\"M100,450 C 400,350 600,550 800,450 C 1000,350 1200,550 1500,450\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#d1d5db\" stroke-width=\"50\"/>\n                    <path d=\"M100,450 C 400,350 600,550 800,450 C 1000,350 1200,550 1500,450\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"white\" stroke-width=\"5\" stroke-dasharray=\"30 30\"/>\n                    <!-- Checkpoints -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(300, 350)\">\n                        <circle cx=\"0\" cy=\"0\" r=\"20\" fill=\"#22c55e\"/>\n                        <text y=\"-40\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"24\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Checkpoint A</text>\n                        <text y=\"60\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"20\" fill=\"#15803d\" text-anchor=\"middle\">console.log(\"A\")</text>\n                    </g>\n                     <g transform=\"translate(800, 450)\">\n                        <circle cx=\"0\" cy=\"0\" r=\"20\" fill=\"#22c55e\"/>\n                        <text y=\"-40\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"24\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Checkpoint B</text>\n                        <text y=\"60\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"20\" fill=\"#15803d\" text-anchor=\"middle\">console.log(\"B\")</text>\n                    </g>\n                     <g transform=\"translate(1300, 500)\">\n                        <circle cx=\"0\" cy=\"0\" r=\"20\" fill=\"#22c55e\"/>\n                        <text y=\"-40\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"24\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Checkpoint C</text>\n                        <text y=\"60\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"20\" fill=\"#15803d\" text-anchor=\"middle\">console.log(\"C\")</text>\n                    </g>\n                </svg>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-8\">\n                    When your browser runs your JavaScript file, it's like going on a long road trip, following the directions in your code from top to bottom. But because it happens so fast, it's easy to get lost and not know which part of the \"trip\" your code is currently on, especially if there's a problem.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4\">\n                    Using <code class=\"bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-1 rounded\">console.log()</code> is like shouting \"We're here!\" every time you pass a major landmark. You can put <code class=\"bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-1 rounded\">console.log(\"Reached the user validation function\")</code> or <code class=\"bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-1 rounded\">console.log(\"Now calculating total\")</code> at different points. By looking at the messages printed in your console, you can trace the exact path your program took and see the last \"town\" it passed through before it broke down.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-tagline mt-6 text-center font-semibold text-sky-600 italic\">`console.log()` is your code's way of telling you exactly where it is on its journey.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        \n        <!-- Tab 5 Content: The Lighthouse Beam -->\n        <div class=\"tab-content content5\" id=\"content5\">\n            <h3 class=\"intro-title text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3\">The Lighthouse Beam</h3>\n            <h2 class=\"intro-question text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4\">You are a ship in a vast, dark ocean. How do you find your way and avoid danger?</h2>\n            <div class=\"description-container flex flex-col justify-center w-full mb-6 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg shadow-inner\">\n                 <svg width=\"100%\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"bg-white rounded-md shadow-sm\">\n                    <rect width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" fill=\"#0f172a\" />\n                    <!-- Lighthouse (Console) -->\n                    <g transform=\"translate(800, 450)\">\n                        <polygon points=\"-50,300 50,300 80,0 -80,0\" fill=\"#e5e7eb\"/>\n                        <rect x=\"-100\" y=\"0\" width=\"200\" height=\"50\" fill=\"#dc2626\"/>\n                        <!-- Beam -->\n                        <path d=\"M0,0 L -800,-300 L -800,-350 L 0,-50 Z\" fill=\"#fde047\" opacity=\"0.5\">\n                            <animateTransform attributeName=\"transform\" type=\"rotate\" from=\"0 0 0\" to=\"360 0 0\" dur=\"10s\" repeatCount=\"indefinite\"/>\n                        </path>\n                    </g>\n                    <text x=\"800\" y=\"800\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"32\" font-weight=\"bold\" fill=\"white\" text-anchor=\"middle\">The Console</text>\n                    <!-- Ship (You, the developer) -->\n                     <g transform=\"translate(200, 600)\">\n                        <path d=\"M-100,0 L 100,0 C 80,50 -80,50 -100,0 Z\" fill=\"#a16207\"/>\n                     </g>\n                </svg>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-8\">\n                    Writing code without a way to see what's happening internally is like navigating a ship in the dark. You know your destination, but you can't see the rocks, the currents, or where you are. You are sailing completely blind, hoping you don't crash.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-explanation text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-4\">\n                    The Developer Console is your lighthouse. The command <code class=\"bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 px-1 rounded\">console.log()</code> is a powerful beam of light that you can shine from your code into that darkness. It illuminates what's happening, reveals hidden values, and most importantly, warns you of danger by printing bright red error messages when you're headed for the rocks. It is the single most important tool for navigating the complexities of your code safely.\n                </p>\n                <p class=\"intro-tagline mt-6 text-center font-semibold text-sky-600 italic\">Let `console.log()` be the lighthouse that guides your code through the dark.</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n<!--end-of-code-block-->",
